## Setup Guide

### 1. Install n8n via Docker (WSL)

```bash
mkdir ~/n8n && cd ~/n8n
nano docker-compose.yml
docker compose up -d
docker ps
```

Access n8n at `http://localhost:5678`

---

### 2. Configure FIM on Wazuh Agent

Edit `/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf` on the agent:

```xml
<directories check_all="yes" report_changes="yes" realtime="yes">/root</directories>
```

```bash
sudo systemctl restart wazuh-agent
```

Test: `touch /root/testfile.txt` — verify alert in Wazuh dashboard.

---

### 3. Deploy Integration Script on Manager

```bash
sudo cp custom-n8n /var/ossec/integrations/custom-n8n
sudo chmod 750 /var/ossec/integrations/custom-n8n
sudo chown root:wazuh /var/ossec/integrations/custom-n8n
```

---

### 4. Add Integration Block on Manager

Edit `/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf` — add before first `</ossec_config>`:

```xml
<integration>
  <name>custom-n8n</name>
  <hook_url>http://WSL_IP:5678/webhook/wazuh-fim</hook_url>
  <rule_id>100201</rule_id>
  <alert_format>json</alert_format>
</integration>
```

> Replace `WSL_IP` with your actual WSL IP (`hostname -I` inside WSL). This IP can change on reboot.

```bash
sudo systemctl restart wazuh-manager
```

---

### 5. n8n Workflow Nodes

| # | Node | Config |
|---|------|--------|
| 1 | Webhook | Method: POST, Path: wazuh-fim, Respond: When Last Node Finishes |
| 2 | Edit Fields | Maps FIM fields from alert JSON (see table below) |
| 3 | HTTP Request | GET VirusTotal — `https://www.virustotal.com/api/v3/files/{{$json.sha256}}` |
| 4 | HTTP Request | POST ntfy — `https://ntfy.sh/your-topic` |

**Edit Fields mappings:**

| Field | Expression |
|-------|-----------|
| hostname | `{{$json.body.agent.name}}` |
| agent_ip | `{{$json.body.agent.ip}}` |
| filename | `{{$json.body.syscheck.path}}` |
| username | `{{$json.body.syscheck.uname_after}}` |
| md5 | `{{$json.body.syscheck.md5_after}}` |
| sha256 | `{{$json.body.syscheck.sha256_after}}` |
| event_type | `{{$json.body.syscheck.event}}` |

Publish the workflow (toggle Active) before testing.

